          <h2>Bitcoin: The Origin of Cryptocurrencies</h2>
          
          <p>Cryptocurrencies are digital currency that was initially introduced to the world by <strong>Satoshi Nakamoto</strong> in the year 2009. The first cryptocurrency created was <em>BITCOIN</em> which crowned the success of a new technology known as the <strong>Blockchain Technology</strong>.</p>
          
          <p>There are over 11,000 crytocurrencies in the world but they are divided into two groups which are,
              <ol>
              <li><strong>BITCOIN</strong></li>
              <li><strong>ALTCOIN</strong></li>
              </p>
          <br
          <p>Note: Altcoins are every other coins that is not bitcoin.</p>
        <p>The image below gives an overview of the blockchain technology</p>  
          <img src="img/blockchain12.png" alt="An image showing how the blockchain technology works">
          
          <p>There are terminologies frequently used in the cryptocurrecy space, they are listed below</p>
          <ul>
              <li>FOMO: FEAR OF MISSING OUT</li>
              <li>BULL: Upward movement of the market</li>
              <li>BEAR: Downward movement of the market</li>
              <li>DIP: A downward market plunge</li>
              <li>HODL: Hold on to dear life</li>
              <li>FUD: Fear uncertainty and doubt</li>
              <li>OTC: Over the counter etc.</li>
           </ul>
